Wash and dry produce. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}, separating whites from greens.

Open package of @diced chicken thighs{20%ounces} and drain off any excess liquid. Heat a drizzle of @oil{1%teaspoon} in a large #pot{} over medium-high heat. Add chicken, scallion whites, @Mexican spice blend{1%tablespoon}, @garlic powder{1%teaspoon}, @salt{}, and @pepper{}; stir to combine. Cook, stirring occasionally, until chicken is browned but not yet cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Stir in @crushed tomatoes{13.76%ounces}, @chicken stock concentrate{1}, ½ cup water, @sugar{½%teaspoon}, and 1 tsp salt. Bring to a boil, then reduce to a low simmer and cover. Cook, undisturbed, until chicken is cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}.

> For 8 servings, use 1 cup water, 1 tsp sugar, 2 tsp salt.

Meanwhile, drain and rinse @black beans{1}. Transfer beans to a medium #bowl{}; mash with a #fork{} until mostly smooth.

Once chicken is cooked through, turn off heat. Using a #slotted spoon{}, transfer chicken to bowl with mashed beans. Stir to combine; taste and season with salt and pepper if desired. Reserve cooking liquid in pot for Step 5.

Place a small amount of filling on one half of each @flour tortillas{12}. Roll up tortillas, starting with filled sides, to create enchiladas. Arrange, seam sides down, in a #9-by-13-inch baking dish{}.

Adjust rack to top position; heat broiler to high. Return #pot{} with reserved cooking liquid to medium-high heat. Whisk in @enchilada sauce{10%ounces} and bring to a low simmer. Cook, whisking constantly, until incorporated, ~{1-2%minutes}.

> TIP: Add a pinch of chili flakes or a dash of your favorite hot sauce if you like things spicy!

Pour sauce over enchiladas to coat (if you like less saucy enchiladas, feel free to use less!). Sprinkle evenly with @Mexican cheese blend{1%cup}. Broil on top rack until sauce is bubbly and cheese is melted and browned, ~{3-5%minutes}.

Divide enchiladas between plates. Sprinkle with reserved scallion greens and dollop with @sour cream{3%tablespoons}. Serve.

> Chicken is fully cooked when internal temperature reaches 165°.